The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Durgapur, July 16: An engineering students co-passengers on the Dhanbad-bound Black Diamond Express mistook a computer gadget in his luggage as an explosive device, trigg-ering a bomb scare. 

 Police said the computer engineering student of National Institute of Technology, Durgapur, was away from his seat in the AC chair car for about an hour when his black bag aroused suspicion. Scared, one of the passengers pulled the chain at Mankar, 150 km from Calcutta.

 The police had informed the army camp at nearby Panagarh when the boy returned from another compartment, where he was with other college friends and identified his bag and books, thought to be bomb-making literature.

 Krishnagar: BSF and BDR jawans exchanged fire this morning in Nadias Chapra, about 140 km from Calcutta. The skirmish began after an alleged smuggler was gunned down by Indian jawans. As in Gede, also in Nadia, last month when about 10,000 rounds were fired. Then the BDR had claimed that its jawans thought they were being fired upon.

 Calcutta: Mamata Banerjee will sow seeds of aman paddy in a field at Singur in Hooghly on Tuesday. The Trinamul Congress chief is oppo-sing the acquisition of farmland for a Tata car factory at Singur, about 40 km from Calcutta.




